frameDefinitions: An Entity is undergoing a change in age typically associated with some deterioration or change in state.
An Entity changes from a Prior_state to a Post_state in a sequence that follows a pre-defined plan, expectation, or model of change.
An Entity has existed for a length of time, the Age.
An Entity is at a particular stage of its development.

A Manner describes general or specific characteristics of an event in one of three ways:  First, it can refer to how a Comparison_event transpires, absent the influence of an entity (e.g. 'the way you talk').
frameExamples: Their offensive armament has <t>developed</t> from short range missiles to long-range ballistic weaponry in a relatively short period .
This building is twenty thousand years <t>old</t>.
The <t>Next Generation</t> Internet (NGI) Program has been successfully completed.
He completed the task in a fervent <t>manner</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: This role indicates where the <fen>Entity</fen> is located.
The time at which the progress occurs.
The location where the Progress occurs.
The <fen>Entity</fen> for which a particular age is under consideration.
The feature of an <fen>Entity</fen> which is a function of the amount of time that the <fen>Entity</fen> has existed.
A quantity or other characterization of the <fen>Entity</fen>'s age.
A modifier expressing  the deviation of the <fen>Age</fen> from the norm.
The Frame Element <fen>Expressor</fen> marks expressions that indicate a body part, gesture or other expression of the <fen>Entity</fen> that reflect its age.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is at a particular <fen>Age</fen>.
The object that has reached a particular stage of its development.
The time at which the progress occurs.

The <fen>Comparison_event</fen> is the principal event being characteriszed by the <fen>Manner</fen>. The <fen>Manner</fen> of this <fen>Comparison_event</fen> is often used in comparison with the <fen>Foreground_event</fen>.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> that is associated with or directly responsible for the <fen>Comparison_activity</fen>.
The <fen>Salient_entity</fen> conducts or engages in the <fen>Comparison_activity</fen> that is being described.
